theorem Topology.dense_interior_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Dense (interior A) → Dense (interior (closure A)) := by
  intro hDense
  -- Unfold `Dense` in the hypothesis and goal to work with equalities.
  unfold Dense at hDense ⊢
  -- `interior A ⊆ interior (closure A)`, since `closure A` contains `A`.
  have h_subset : interior A ⊆ interior (closure A) := by
    apply interior_mono
    exact subset_closure
  -- Taking closures preserves the inclusion.
  have h_closure_subset :
      closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) :=
    closure_mono h_subset
  -- Every point belongs to `closure (interior (closure A))`.
  have h_univ_subset : (Set.univ : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) := by
    intro x hx
    -- Using the density of `interior A`.
    have : x ∈ closure (interior A) := by
      simpa [hDense] using hx
    exact h_closure_subset this
  -- Establish the required equality of sets.
  have h_eq : closure (interior (closure A)) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    apply Set.Subset.antisymm
    · intro x _; trivial
    · exact h_univ_subset
  simpa using h_eq

theorem Topology.closure_interior_closure_subset_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure A := by
  -- First, `interior (closure A)` is contained in `closure A`.
  have h : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A := interior_subset
  -- Taking closures preserves inclusions; simplify `closure (closure A)`.
  simpa [closure_closure] using closure_mono h
